</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Sexless Drood Watchman</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(11/27/01 11:11:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revised Vox Strategy and loot rules *please read*</span><hr size=1> One enchanter makes it possible.  But you are still very marginal even if the enchanter is 52.<br>
<br>
Certainly they can stand farther away.  I believe Mana Sieve is one of the few spells that can be cast at max distance from Vox and still take effect.  However, they are still suseptable to Fear.  A feared enchanter is a useless enchanter and if they are feared even 50 percent of the time, they're not casting for that period.  Also, even if they are never feared, they can only cast 1 spell at a time.<br>
<br>
The reason for failure against Vox isnt combat power or resists or even fear.  The reason for failure against Vox is that she Complete Heals.  Pretty much the only reason.  Which of course is why you have enchanters.  But you almost are required to have multiple ones so that there is always at least 1 casting mana sieve or theft of thought at all times, preferably all of them.  It'll take between 4-5 of them generally to sieve her mana.  And if these fights arent over within a minute or so you'll once again probably lose because she'll have killed enough tanks that your casters are again dead meat when she Cheals.<br>
<br>
Bottom line.  No enchanters and I'll give you maybe a 10percent chance at success.  For each enchanter after that you can add about 20-25 percent up to 3.  Past 3 and I dont think they'll add much more than simply accelerate an already fast happening event.  One enchanter certainly can do the job.  However, it is not so great a margin that delaying the raid an hour for an additional enchanter or two isnt worthwhile.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
KCoG Plane Raid Liason <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umordethshadowbreeze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordeth Shadowbreeze</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/17/01 2:35:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/krwilson/pics/mordeth.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revised Vox Strategy and loot rules *please read*</span><hr size=1> I have one suggestion for the Next Vox raid, concerning Buffing. I was at the last Vox raid and I really liked some of the tactics. Having a group go and clear out the IGs before hand was a great idea, as was having a high level task force doing the Buff line. That being said, I was at the end of the buff line and by the time i got to the end my Shammy buffs were already flashing. So, here is my suggestion.<br>
Since most groups (if not all) will usually have at least one buffer in the group have them do the first &quot;throw away buffs&quot;. All that should remain for the Buff Line (for Tanks at least) is:<br>
cleric HP/Symbol Buffs; RM/RC Buffs (can be done either by cleric/Shammy/druid I believe with Druid being the best option due to Circle of X - should one or two of high enough level be around); and finally Haste Buffs from the chanter. I think this could greatly accelerate the Buff Line process...<br>
